properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A late season snowfall in store for some regions of the province. Total snowfall: up to 10 cm for some areas, possibly more especially over the Cape Breton Highlands.. Maximum wind gusts: 70 to 90 km/h, Location: northern and western Nova Scotia. Time span: tonight into Sunday. Remarks: Periods of snow and strong winds are expected to develop this evening over western Nova Scotia where westerly winds blow onshore. These conditions are forecast to spread eastward across northern Nova Scotia later tonight, reaching the Cape Breton Highlands during the overnight hours. Conditions will improve Sunday morning over western areas of the province, and later in the morning or in the afternoon over eastern regions. Large waves, pounding surf and elevated sea levels are expected. Locations: the Nova Scotia coastline of the Bay of Fundy, including the Minas Basin. Time Span: from 11:00 p.m. this evening to 3:00 am on Sunday. Remarks: An intensifying low pressure system will pass just north of Nova Scotia today. This will give storm surge combined with waves approaching the Fundy coast of the province from the west, as well as large spring tides this weekend. The combined effects may cause minor flooding. If the storm track or intensity changes, storm surge warnings may be required. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NSstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NSStorm.

properties.Title: Weather Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Weather travel advisory in effect for this morning and early this afternoon. Brief but intense lake effect snow bands off Georgian Bay will bring low visibility in heavy snow to the areas today. Conditions will improve this afternoon. Motorists should note that in lake effect snow, conditions can vary from no snow to very low visibility in heavy snow in a very short distance. Be prepared for rapid changes in weather and road conditions. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.

properties.Summary:

properties.Title: Frost Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Near or below freezing temperatures tonight through early Wednesday. Hazard: Frost and freeze conditions. Timing: This morning and tonight. Likely again Monday night and Tuesday night. Impact: Frost sensitive crops and plants could be damaged or killed by frost. Action: Take preventive measures to protect frost sensitive crops and plants. An extended period of significantly colder than normal temperatures will result in several days of frost and, at times, hard freezes across much of Southern Ontario. These conditions are expected to persist through Wednesday morning. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.
